						<summary>

						<p>On a <hi rend="italic">Garuḍa</hi> pillar set up in front of the Chennakēśvasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1489 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated Śaka 1410, Saumya, Chaitra, ba. 30. The cyclic year, month and day falls on 1489 A.D. and the date of the record corresponds to 1489 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Records that certain Yallāpregaḍa Devarāju presented an (image of) Garutmanta to the temple of Kēśavanātha.</p>						

						</summary>
